title: Seychelles Food Inflation
description: Cost of food in Seychelles increased 2.45 percent in October of 2022 over the same month in the previous year. Food Inflation in Seychelles averaged 7.93 percent from 2007 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 74.32 percent in December of 2008 and a record low of -11.41 percent in March of 2010. This page provides - Seychelles Food Inflation - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: National Bureau of Statistics, Seychelles
